BEGIN_PGML
Find a vector equation for the line segment from [`(1,2,3)`] to [`(3,2,1)\text{.}`]

[`\vec{r}(t) =`] [_]{$multians}{15} [@AnswerFormatHelp('vectors')@]* for [_]{$multians}{3} [`\leq t \leq `] [_]{$multians}{3}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Hint
############################################################
#Set value of $showHint in PGcourse.pl for course-wide attempt threshhold for revealing hints

BEGIN_PGML_HINT
Recall that a vector equation for a line segment from point [`P`] to point [`Q`] is [`\vec{r}(t)=\vec{P} +\vec{PQ}t`] for [`0\leq t\leq 1`] where [`\vec{P}`] is the position vector with head at point [`P`] and [`\vec{PQ}`] is the vector pointing from [`P`] to [`Q\text{.}`]

END_PGML_HINT

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The vector pointing from [`(1,2,3)`] to [`(3,2,1)`] is [`\vec{v}=2\vec{i} -2\vec{k}\text{.}`] Therefore, a vector equation for this line segment will be

[```
                                    \vec{r}(t)=\vec{i} +2\vec{j} +3\vec{k} +(2\vec{i} -2\vec{k})t=(1+2t)\vec{i} +2\vec{j} +(3-2t)\vec{k}
                                ```]

with [`0\leq t\leq 1\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

############################################################
# End Problem
############################################################

ENDDOCUMENT();

setup.pg-code:
Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are(t=>"Real");
Context()->variables->set(t=>{limits=>[-1,1]});

$x = Formula("3*cos(t)");
$y = Formula("3*sin(t)");
$t0 = Compute("0");
$t1 = Compute("pi/2");

($x0,$y0) = (3,0);
($x1,$y1) = (0,3);

$multians = MultiAnswer($x, $y, $t0, $t1)->with(
  singleResult => 0,
  checker => sub {
      my ( $correct, $student, $self ) = @_;
      my ( $xstu, $ystu, $t0stu, $t1stu ) = @{$student};
      if ( 
           ( ( sqrt(9-($xstu)**2) - ($ystu) ) == 0 )  and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $x0 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $y0 ) and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $x1 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $y1 )
         ) {
            return [1,1,1,1];

      } elsif (
           ( ( sqrt(9-($xstu)**2) - ($ystu) ) == 0 )  and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $x0 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $y0 ) 
         ) { 
            return [1,1,1,0];

      } elsif (
           ( ( sqrt(9-($xstu)**2) - ($ystu) ) == 0 )  and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $x1 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $y1 )
         ) { 
            return [1,1,0,1];

      } elsif (
           ( ( sqrt(9-($xstu)**2) - ($ystu) ) == 0 ) 
         ) { 
            return [1,1,0,0];

      } else {
            return [0,0,0,0];
      }
  }
);

