BEGIN_PGML
Find a vector equation for a half circle centered at [`(1,4,1)`] of radius [`2`] in the plane [`y=4`] starting at the point [`(3,4,1)\text{.}`]

[`x(t) =`] [_]{$multians}{10} [@AnswerFormatHelp('formulas')@]*

[`y(t) =`] [_]{$multians}{10} [@AnswerFormatHelp('formulas')@]*

[`z(t) =`] [_]{$multians}{10} [@AnswerFormatHelp('formulas')@]*

for [_]{$multians}{3} [`\leq t \leq `] [_]{$multians}{3} [@AnswerFormatHelp('numbers')@]*

END_PGML

############################################################
# Hint
############################################################
#Set value of $showHint in PGcourse.pl for course-wide attempt threshhold for revealing hints

BEGIN_PGML_HINT
The equation [`\vec{r}(t) =\cos t \vec{i} +\sin t \vec{k}\text{,}`] [`0\leq t\leq 2\pi`] gives a full circle oriented counter-clockwise starting (when [`t=0`]) at [`(1,0)`] in the [`xz`]-plane. How can you modify this vector equation to give the described circle?

END_PGML_HINT

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The equation [`\vec{r}(t) =\cos t \vec{i} +\sin t \vec{k}\text{,}`] [`0\leq t\leq 2\pi`] gives a full circle oriented counter-clockwise starting (when [`t=0`]) at [`(1,0,0)`] in the [`xz`]-plane. To get a circle of radius [`2\text{,}`] we scale each component by [`2\text{,}`] and to move the center to [`(1,4,1)`] we add the vector [`\vec{i} +4\vec{j}+\vec{k}`] (which translates every point in the [`x`]-direction by [`1\text{,}`] the [`y`]-direction by [`4`] and the [`z`]-direction by [`1`]).  Thus

[```
                                    \vec{r}(t) =(1+2\cos t)\vec{i} +4\vec{j}+(1+ 2\sin(t))\vec{k}
                                ```]

for [`0\leq t\leq 2\pi`] is a circle of radius [`2`] centered at  [`(1,4,1)`] in the plane [`y=4`] starting at the point [`(3,2,1)\text{.}`]  To get the half circle, we restrict [`0\leq t\leq \pi\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

############################################################
# End Problem
############################################################

ENDDOCUMENT();

