p.me:
\begin{aligned}
      \int_{0}^{1} (e^x+x^2) \sqrt{{11}} dx \amp =  \sqrt{{11}} \int_{0}^{1} e^x+ \sqrt{{11}}\int_{0}^{1} x^2 dx\\
       \amp = \sqrt{{11}} \left( e^x\right)_{0}^{1}  + \sqrt{{11}}\left( \frac{x^3}{3} \right)_{0}^1 \\
       \amp = \sqrt{{11}} ( e-1) + \sqrt{{11}}\left(\frac{1}{3} -0\right) \\
       \amp = \frac{\sqrt{{11}}}{3}(3e-2)
      \end{aligned}

setup.pg-code:
