BEGIN_PGML Evaluate [`\displaystyle \int_{C} \left( z\vec{i} -y\vec{j}+x\vec{k} \right) \cdot d\vec{r}`] where [`C`] is the line segment from [`(5,0,2)`] to [`(5,3,4)\text{.}`]
The line segment from [`(5,0,2)`] to [`(5,3,4)`] can be parameterized by
[`\vec{r}(t)=`] [_]{$multians}{15} [@AnswerFormatHelp('vectors')@]* for [_]{$multians}{3} [`\leq t \leq`] [_]{$multians}{3}.
Thus,
[`\displaystyle \int_{C} \left( z\vec{i} -y\vec{j}+x\vec{k} \right) \cdot d\vec{r}=`] [_]{$integral}{10} [@AnswerFormatHelp('numbers')@]*
END_PGML
############################################################ # Hint ############################################################ #Set value of $showHint in PGcourse.pl for course-wide attempt threshhold for revealing hints
BEGIN_PGML_HINT Parametrize the curve and remember that if [`\vec{r}(t)\text{,}`] for [`a\leq t\leq b\text{,}`] is a smooth parameterization of an oriented curve [`C`] and [`\vec{F}`] is a vector field which is continuous on [`C\text{,}`] then
[``` \int_C \vec{F}\cdot d\vec{r}=\int_a^b \vec{F}(\vec{r}(t))\cdot \vec{r}'(t) dt. ```]
END_PGML_HINT
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION Remember that if [`\vec{r}(t)\text{,}`] for [`a\leq t\leq b\text{,}`] is a smooth parameterization of an oriented curve [`C`] and [`\vec{F}`] is a vector field which is continuous on [`C\text{,}`] then
[``` \int_C \vec{F}\cdot d\vec{r}=\int_a^b \vec{F}(\vec{r}(t))\cdot \vec{r}'(t) dt. ```]
The line segment from [`(5,0,2)`] to [`(5,3,4)`] can be parameterized by
[``` \vec{r}(t)=5\vec{i} +3t\vec{j}+(2t+2)\vec{k},\quad 0\leq t\leq 1 ```]
and we have
[``` \vec{r}'(t)=3\vec{j} +2\vec{k}. ```]
Thus,
[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}\begin{aligned} \int_{C} \left( z\vec{i} -y\vec{j}+x\vec{k} \right) \cdot d\vec{r} \amp = \int_0^1 \left( (2t+2)\vec{i}-3t\vec{j}+5\vec{k}\right) \cdot \left(3\vec{j}+2\vec{k} \right)dt\\ \amp = \int_0^1 (-9t+10) dt \\ \amp = \left( -\frac{9t^2}{2}+10t\right)_{0}^{1}\\ \amp = 5.5. \end{aligned}```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();

setup.pg-code:
$integral=Compute("1/6*(3*e^4-19)");

Context()->variables->are(t=>"Real");
Context()->variables->set(t=>{limits=>[-5,5]});

$x = Formula("-t");
$y = Formula("e^(-t)");
$t0 = Compute("-2");
$t1 = Compute("0");

($x0,$y0) = (2,exp(2));
($x1,$y1) = (0,1);

$multians = MultiAnswer($x, $y, $t0, $t1)->with(
  singleResult => 0,
  checker => sub {
      my ( $correct, $student, $self ) = @_;
      my ( $xstu, $ystu, $t0stu, $t1stu ) = @{$student};
      if ( 
           ( ((exp(1))**($xstu) - ($ystu)) == 0 )  and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $x0 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $y0 ) and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $x1 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $y1 )
         ) {
            return [1,1,1,1];

      } elsif (
           ( ((exp(1))**($xstu) - ($ystu)) == 0 )   and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $x0 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t0stu)) == $y0 ) 
         ) { 
            return [1,1,1,0];

      } elsif (
           ( ((exp(1))**($xstu) - ($ystu)) == 0 )   and
           ( ($xstu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $x1 ) and
           ( ($ystu->eval(t=>$t1stu)) == $y1 )
         ) { 
            return [1,1,0,1];

      } elsif (
           ( ((exp(1))**($xstu) - ($ystu)) == 0 )  
         ) { 
            return [1,1,0,0];

      } else {
            return [0,0,0,0];
      }
  }
);

